import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load the Titanic dataset
titanic_df = pd.read_csv('C:\\Users\\johnm\\OneDrive\\Desktop\\train.csv')

# Display the first few rows of the dataset
print(titanic_df.head())

# Display dataset information
print(titanic_df.info())

# Display summary statistics
print(titanic_df.describe())

# Data Cleaning

# Handle missing values
print(titanic_df.isnull().sum())
titanic_df['Age'].fillna(titanic_df['Age'].median(), inplace=True)
titanic_df['Embarked'].fillna(titanic_df['Embarked'].mode()[0], inplace=True)

# Check unique values in 'Sex' and 'Embarked' columns
print("Unique values in 'Sex' column:", titanic_df['Sex'].unique())
print("Unique values in 'Embarked' column:", titanic_df['Embarked'].unique())

# Convert data types if necessary
# Ensure the mapping values in 'Sex' and 'Embarked' are correctly matched
sex_mapping = {'male': 0, 'female': 1}
embarked_mapping = {'C': 0, 'Q': 1, 'S': 2}

titanic_df['Sex'] = titanic_df['Sex'].map(sex_mapping)
titanic_df['Embarked'] = titanic_df['Embarked'].map(embarked_mapping)

# Verify mapping
print(titanic_df[['Sex', 'Embarked']].head())

# Drop columns that won't be used in the analysis
titanic_df.drop(['Name', 'Ticket', 'Cabin'], axis=1, inplace=True)

# Display the cleaned dataset
print(titanic_df.head())

# Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

# Correlation matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(titanic_df.corr(), annot=True, cmap='coolwarm')
plt.title('Correlation Matrix')
plt.show()

# Distribution of numerical features
titanic_df.hist(bins=20, figsize=(14, 10), color='steelblue', edgecolor='black')
plt.suptitle('Distribution of Numerical Features')
plt.show()

# Survived count plot
sns.countplot(x='Survived', data=titanic_df)
plt.title('Survival Count')
plt.show()

# Survival rate by sex
sns.barplot(x='Sex', y='Survived', data=titanic_df)
plt.title('Survival Rate by Sex')
plt.show()

# Survival rate by class
sns.barplot(x='Pclass', y='Survived', data=titanic_df)
plt.title('Survival Rate by Class')
plt.show()

# Age distribution by survival
sns.kdeplot(titanic_df[titanic_df['Survived'] == 0]['Age'], shade=True, label='Not Survived')
sns.kdeplot(titanic_df[titanic_df['Survived'] == 1]['Age'], shade=True, label='Survived')
plt.title('Age Distribution by Survival')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Pair plot of features
sns.pairplot(titanic_df, hue='Survived')
plt.suptitle('Pair Plot of Features', y=1.02)
plt.show()
